The United States announced export controls on 11 Chinese companies and scientific research institutions. These entities were included in the export control list for obtaining or attempting to obtain U.S. controlled items to support China's military modernization. Including missile and hypersonic weapons projects.
Among them, Thunder Micropower Technology Co., Ltd. provided precision-guided missiles and satellite communication systems to the People's Liberation Army of China;
Chengdu Yaguang Electronics Co., Ltd. and its parent company Yaguang Technology Group Co., Ltd. provided dual-use electronic components to the People's Liberation Army of China and multiple Chinese parties on the Entity List;
Hefei Xingbo Communication Technology Co., Ltd. provided RF/microwave products clearly used for military equipment to the People's Liberation Army and Chinese parties on the Entity List.
